:"https://blog.greg.technology/2025/11/27/github-should-charge-1-dollar-more-per-month.html","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"bt","user_is_author":false,"tags":["rant"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/na5mij","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/na5mij/github_should_charge_everyone_1_more_per"},{"short_id":"aqk7vl","created_at":"2026-06-17T08:23:44.000-05:00","title":"Pull Requests are Free Puppies","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x8_ZZhRL3YU\u0026t=1733s","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eLightly edited transcript of Richard Hipp, creator of SQLite, from 28'53\":\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSuppose you had a pull request for SQLite. \"Hey, I've got this new feature for SQLite. Here's the pull request.\" When you want me to pull that into the tree, you say, \"Oh, it's free.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNo, it's not free. What you're doing is asking me - you've got this cool feature, and you want me to maintain it for you, to document it for you, to test it for you, to maintain it for you for the next twenty-five years. That's not free.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLinus Torvalds is famous for saying there's free as in beer and free as in speech. But there's another kind of freedom: free as in puppies. \"Oh look, I've got a free puppy for you.\" You see where this is going?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA pull request is a free puppy. And then you've just got a kennel full of puppies at the end of the day. And you can't just throw them out - you're morally obligated to take care of them for their natural life.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI don't want any free puppies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n","description_plain":"Lightly edited transcript of Richard Hipp, creator of SQLite, from 28'53\":\r\n\u003e Suppose you had a pull request for SQLite. \"Hey, I've got this new feature for SQLite. Here's the pull request.\" When you want me to pull that into the tree, you say, \"Oh, it's free.\"  \r\n\u003e  \r\n\u003e No, it's not free. What you're doing is asking me - you've got this cool feature, and you want me to maintain it for you, to document it for you, to test it for you, to maintain it for you for the next twenty-five years. That's not free.  \r\n\u003e  \r\n\u003e Linus Torvalds is famous for saying there's free as in beer and free as in speech. But there's another kind of freedom: free as in puppies. \"Oh look, I've got a free puppy for you.\" You see where this is going?  \r\n\u003e  \r\n\u003e A pull request is a free puppy. And then you've just got a kennel full of puppies at the end of the day. And you can't just throw them out - you're morally obligated to take care of them for their natural life.  \r\n\u003e  \r\n\u003e I don't want any free puppies.","submitter_user":"ndr","user_is_author":false,"tags":["programming","video"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aqk7vl","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aqk7vl/pull_requests_are_free_puppies"},{"short_id":"nh9q9g","created_at":"2026-06-17T07:20:21.000-05:00","title":"R Core team wins Rousseeuw Prize for Statistics 2026","url":"https://rousseeuwprize.org/2026","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"eddelbuettel","user_is_author":false,"tags":["programming","science"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nh9q9g","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/nh9q9g/r_core_team_wins_rousseeuw_prize_for"},{"short_id":"hnoijy","created_at":"2026-06-17T05:45:54.000-05:00","title":"Color picking Oklch for mortals","url":"https://hugodaniel.com/posts/color-picking-oklch/","score":12,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"HugoDaniel","user_is_author":true,"tags":["design","graphics"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hnoijy","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hnoijy/color_picking_oklch_for_mortals"},{"short_id":"l6xs1q","created_at":"2026-06-17T0